        public static int adjustOffset(PsiFile file,
                               Document document,
                               int offset)
        Attempts to adjust the offset in the file to point to an identifier, single quote, double quote, closing bracket or parentheses by moving it back by a single character. Does nothing if there are no identifiers around, or the offset is already in one.
        Parameters:
        file - language source for the isIdentifierPart(PsiFile, CharSequence, int)
        See Also:

        public static PsiElement findTargetElement(Editor editor,
                                           int flags)
        Note: this method can perform slow PSI activity (e.g. PsiReference.resolve(), so please avoid calling it from Swing thread.
        Parameters:
        editor - editor
        flags - a combination of REFERENCED_ELEMENT_ACCEPTED, ELEMENT_NAME_ACCEPTED
        Returns:
        a PSI element declared or referenced at the specified offset in the editor, depending on the flags passed.
        See Also:
        findTargetElement(Editor, int, int)

      • findTargetElement

        public static PsiElement findTargetElement(Editor editor,
                                           int flags,
                                           int offset)
        Note: this method can perform slow PSI activity (e.g. PsiReference.resolve(), so please avoid calling it from Swing thread.
        Parameters:
        editor - editor
        flags - a combination of REFERENCED_ELEMENT_ACCEPTED, ELEMENT_NAME_ACCEPTED
        offset - offset in the editor's document
        Returns:
        a PSI element declared or referenced at the specified offset in the editor, depending on the flags passed.
